shuffle-grazing
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a controlled grazing system that combines ad hoc, set stocking, and rotational grazing. [Stock are grazed in a specific paddock for a week when the gate is opened to a next paddock. Once all of the stock are out of the former enclosure, the gate is closed behind them, the pattern being repeated around 3-4 paddocks. ]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
